				\begin{document}$${f}_{R}\propto t/{l}^{2}\cdot \sqrt{E/\rho },$$\end{document}fR∝t/l2⋅E/ρ,where fR represented the resonant frequency, t and l denoted the thickness and length of the ShPiP, E and ρ signified the elastic modulus and density, respectively. The sound pressure sensitivity of channels 1–8 at their maximum resonant frequencies was summarized in Fig. 2f. An increase in thickness resulted in a slight decrease in sensitivity, as the channel thickness influenced its deformation magnitude under same sound pressure according to Newton’s second law33. Nevertheless, all channels exhibited sufficiently high-pressure sensitivity (350–530 kPa−1).
